    </thing>
  <thing id="ioUmHeCeSa" name="Helm of Certain Sanity" description="{b}Description{/b}\nCrafted by those who wished to shield their perceptions against mind-bending horrors from beyond, this headgear protects against the loss of mental faculties. Any Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma damage or drain suffered by the wearer is reduced by 2, and the wearer is immune to temporary penalties to these ability scores (e.g., {i}touch of idiocy{/i}). The wearer is also made immune to {i}confusion{/i}, {i}feeblemind{/i}, {i}song of discord{/i}, {i}insanity{/i}, and similar effects and gains a +4 bonus to saving throws against patterns and phantasms.\n\nThese protections come with a price, however, as the {i}helm of certain sanity{/i} also leaves the wearer unable to perceive mythos creatures or spells with the mythos descriptor*, treating them as if they had total concealment at all times. This also makes the wearer immune to gaze attacks or similar sight-based supernatural abilities used by such creatures but also imposes a -20 penalty to Knowledge checks to identify such creatures or their abilities. If the wearer is attacked by a mythos creature or spell*, she can perceive it as if it had concealment, appearing only as a dim, threatening shape, for 1d4 rounds.  \n\n{b}*See the Legendary Games product {i}Tomes of Ancient Knowledge.{/b} {/i}If you are not using that product, Mythos creatures or spells are defined as those that trigger {i}Sanity{/i} checks. See {i}Pathfinder Adventure Path #46: Wake of the Watcher.{/i}" compset="Wondrous" summary="Crafted by those who wished to shield their perceptions against mind-bending horrors from beyond, this headgear protects against the loss of mental faculties.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="50000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="3"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="13"/>
    <usesource source="UmTotM"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipAvail"/>
    <tag group="iSchool" tag="Abjur"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpHead"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioUmHoDeOn" name="Horn of the Deep Ones" description="{b}Description{/b}\nThis horn is crafted from a nautiloid shell, and it is constantly wet with a brackish slime. Its sonorous call summons 1d4+1 skum ({i}Pathfinder RPG Bestiary{/i} &quot;Skum&quot;) to serve the one sounding the horn for 10 minutes or until slain. If the creature sounding the horn has the aquatic or water subtype, the skum gain the benefits of {i}good hope{/i} for as long as they remain. If all of the summoned skum are slain, the horn-sounder must succeed at a DC 10 Fortitude save or be {i}polymorphed{/i} into a skum and bound to the horn&apos;s call." compset="Wondrous" summary="This horn is crafted from a nautiloid shell, and it is constantly wet with a brackish slime.">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="12000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="10"/>
    <usesource source="UmTotM"/>
    <tag group="iSchool" tag="Conjur"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioUmMesMas" name="Mesmeric Mask" description="{b}Description{/b}\nThis transparent mask clings to the wearer&apos;s face, almost imperceptible to inspection (Perception DC 30) or magical examination (DC 30 caster level check to detect its presence). The wearer is immune to {i}charm{/i} and {i}dominate{/i} effects but is immediately aware of them and their source. As an immediate action when targeted with such an effect, the wearer may attempt to deceive the creature using the {i}charm{/i} or {i}dominate{/i} effect into believing it has succeeded (DC 20 Will save negates). If the save is failed, the mask-wearer gains a +20 bonus to Bluff or Perform (acting) skill checks to perpetuate the ruse that they are mentally controlled, and he may choose to accept the telepathic bond that accompanies a {i}dominate{/i} effect." compset="Wondrous" summary="This transparent mask clings to the wearer&apos;s face, almost imperceptible to inspection (Perception DC 30) or magical examination (DC 30 caster level check to detect its presence).">
